Discord color bot
A simple discord bot that lets each member change their own role color using hex codes.

Usage
in channel where you have this bot type:  /color andhex sode for color you want (for example #880808 is my favorite)
the bot will intantly update your roles color. btw only you can ee thi bots reply.

Setup
Instal Node.js  
    download and install from nodejs.org LTS version
Clone the repo and install dependencies
    git clone https://github.com/yourusername color-bot.git
    cd color-bot
    npm install
Create your .env file
    copy env.example to a new file called .env and fill in your bot token:
    DISCORD_TOKEN=your_token_here
    btw DONT share your .env file
Create bot on discord
    Go to  discord.com/developers/applications - new application
    Go to bot tab - add bot - copy the tokens into your .env
    go to OAuth2 - URL generator:
        scopes: bot, applications.commands
        bot permissions:manage roles
    Open the generated URL and invite bot to your server
Set role hierarchy
    in your server: setings - roles - drag bots role above the member roles, discords only lets bots edit roles that are below them.
Run the bot
    node bot.js
you shoud seesometing like:
    Logged in as YourBot#1234
    Slash command registered

Notes
the bot must berunning to work, if youclose the terminal it goes offline.
there may be around 1 minute couldown before it will startworking on discord
